{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:job.18",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 18,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 18",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 18 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.18.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 18:1",
      "text": "Then Bildad the Shuhite answered:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.18.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 18:2",
      "text": "“How long will you hunt for words? Consider, and then we will speak.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.18.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 18:3",
      "text": "Why are we counted as cattle? Why are we stupid in your sight?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.18.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 18:4",
      "text": "You who tear yourself in your anger, shall the earth be forsaken for you, or the rock be removed out of its place?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.18.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 18:5",
      "text": "“Yea, the light of the wicked is put out, and the flame of his fire does not shine.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.18.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 18:6",
      "text": "The light is dark in his tent, and his lamp above him is put out.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.18.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 18:7",
      "text": "His strong steps are shortened and his own schemes throw him down.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.18.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 18:8",
      "text": "For he is cast into a net by his own feet, and he walks on a pitfall.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.18.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 18:9",
      "text": "A trap seizes him by the heel, a snare lays hold of him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.18.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 18:10",
      "text": "A rope is hid for him in the ground, a trap for him in the path.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.18.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 18:11",
      "text": "Terrors frighten him on every side, and chase him at his heels.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.18.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 18:12",
      "text": "His strength is hunger-bitten, and calamity is ready for his stumbling.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.18.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 18:13",
      "text": "By disease his skin is consumed, the first-born of death consumes his limbs.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.18.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 18:14",
      "text": "He is torn from the tent in which he trusted, and is brought to the king of terrors.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.18.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 18:15",
      "text": "In his tent dwells that which is none of his; brimstone is scattered upon his habitation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.18.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 18:16",
      "text": "His roots dry up beneath, and his branches wither above.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.18.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 18:17",
      "text": "His memory perishes from the earth, and he has no name in the street.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.18.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 18:18",
      "text": "He is thrust from light into darkness, and driven out of the world.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.18.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 18:19",
      "text": "He has no offspring or descendant among his people, and no survivor where he used to live.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.18.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 18:20",
      "text": "They of the west are appalled at his day, and horror seizes them of the east.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.18.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 18:21",
      "text": "Surely such are the dwellings of the ungodly, such is the place of him who knows not God.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
